      "content": "If a professional adopts local dress or customs, it signals a willingness to adapt, which is a sign of respect, not unprofessionalism. However, they must do so with an air of confidence, not as a caricature. The key is to blend the local respect with a core of Western executive polish—meaning the local attire should still look intentional and high-quality, not like a costume. Ultimately, the perception shifts from \"Western standard\" to \"culturally intelligent global leader.\"",
      "source": "target",
